<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This new species is the nearest to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. flavilabris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="flavilabris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. flavilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Briet, 1917) but can be distinguished by the shape of pronotal marking: 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. flavilabris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="flavilabris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. flavilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the metallic blue marking rhombic, whereas in the new species this marking is not. Additionally, the anterior margin of the clypeus in the new species is yellowish brown but black in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. flavilabris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="flavilabris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. flavilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
