</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Head small, with dense and coarse punctures. Mandibles (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Smaragdina hejingensis Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A habitus B mandibles C maxilla D labium E dorsal view of aedeagus F lateral view of aedeagus G ventral view of aedeagus H spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.74323.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/634777" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2B</figureCitation>
) short, labrum slightly incised at anterior margin, length ratio of maxillary palpomeres 0.5:2.4:1.5:2.4; while that of labial palpomeres 0.5:1.8:2.8; mentum rectangular emarginated at anterior margin. Clypeus lateral sides slightly depressed, anterior margin feebly incised; frons covered with shallow wrinkles; inner sides of eyes with short pubescence; vertex not convex, with fine wrinkles. Antennae short, extending to base of prothorax, pubescent, 1st antennomere oblong, 2nd rounded, 3rd slender, slightly longer than 2nd, 4th triangular, a little longer than 3rd, serrated from 5th segment onwards.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.74323.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/634777" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Smaragdina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Smaragdina hejingensis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hejingensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Smaragdina hejingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
