</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Pronotum transverse, about 2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long, moderately convex; anterior margin slightly convex, lateral margins rounded, posterior margin sinuated, all margins (especially lateral ones) bordered; surface with coarse punctures, denser on median basal area. Scutellum widely triangular, with extremely fine punctures; apex slightly elevated over elytral surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Elytra 1.7 times as long as wide at humeri, covered with confused and dense punctures, interstices shorter than a puncture diameter, punctures becoming sparse posteriorly, and nearly disappearing at elytral apices.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Underside and legs thickly clothed with silvery pubescence; apex of pygidium arcuate. Tarsi slender, length ratio of protarsomeres 1.6:1.0:0.3:2.0. Tibiae of females slightly curved, legs robust, tarsi broad.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Smaragdina hejingensis Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A habitus B lateral view of habitus C spermatheca D lateral view of aedeagus E ventral view of aedeagus F dorsal view of aedeagus G apex of aedeagus H ventral rectal sclerites I dorsal rectal sclerites. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm (C-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.74323.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/634776" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1D-G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Smaragdina hejingensis Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A habitus B mandibles C maxilla D labium E dorsal view of aedeagus F lateral view of aedeagus G ventral view of aedeagus H spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.74323.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/634777" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2E-G</figureCitation>
) sword-shaped, about 3.4
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide; apex triangular; bent ventrally; without pubescence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female.</emphasis>
Coloration of body darker than male, base of hind tibiae black; legs slender, tarsi narrow. Last segment of abdomen with a fossa. Spermatheca (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Smaragdina hejingensis Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A habitus B lateral view of habitus C spermatheca D lateral view of aedeagus E ventral view of aedeagus F dorsal view of aedeagus G apex of aedeagus H ventral rectal sclerites I dorsal rectal sclerites. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm (C-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.74323.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/634776" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Smaragdina hejingensis Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A habitus B mandibles C maxilla D labium E dorsal view of aedeagus F lateral view of aedeagus G ventral view of aedeagus H spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.74323.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/634777" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2H</figureCitation>
) hook-shaped, apex swollen and blunt, duct base thickened, not coiled. Rectal sclerites moderately sclerotized, ventral rectal sclerites (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Smaragdina hejingensis Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A habitus B lateral view of habitus C spermatheca D lateral view of aedeagus E ventral view of aedeagus F dorsal view of aedeagus G apex of aedeagus H ventral rectal sclerites I dorsal rectal sclerites. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm (C-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.74323.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/634776" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1H</figureCitation>
) large, clubbed; dorsal rectal sclerites (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Smaragdina hejingensis Duan, Wang &amp; Zhou, sp. nov. A habitus B lateral view of habitus C spermatheca D lateral view of aedeagus E ventral view of aedeagus F dorsal view of aedeagus G apex of aedeagus H ventral rectal sclerites I dorsal rectal sclerites. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm (C-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.74323.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/634776" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1I</figureCitation>
) protruding medially; lateral sclerites large.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
